# 2. 過去と対峙する勇気

Minori: Bye, Shizuku, Airi! See you after school!
Shizuku: See you later!
Shizuku: Haruka and Minori sounded really excited. And so am I now that we have a meeting date set.
Airi: Same... Minori's apparently so excited that she's been practicing talking every night with her plushies.
Shizuku: Hehe. Really? Minori really does have a wonderful work ethic.
Shizuku: I'll need to do my best as well...
Airi: Yeah... And I'll do my best to try to help you if something does ever come up.
Airi: Still...
Airi: Are you sure about this?
Shizuku: What...?
Airi: About having to appear with Cheerful * Days. You made it seem like everything was fine when Minori and Haruka were with us...
Airi: But my guess is that you don't feel great about this. I mean, they essentially chased you out after saying some really horrible stuff about you...
Shizuku: That's...
Airi: Appearing alongside them means having to talk to them. Face to face.
Airi: No, it's not just that... You also have to keep smiling while in front of the cameras...
Airi: There's no way that's gonna be easy for you. It might feel like ancient history at this point, but you'll be reopening some old and ugly wounds.
Shizuku: Airi...
Airi: So, if you don't feel good about this, please tell me...
Airi: If any part of you is afraid that you're going to ruin our TV appearance... Get that out of your head and don't worry about it.
Shizuku: That's so kind of you, Airi...
Airi: Wh...
Airi: What are you talking about? I'm always kind, aren't I?!
Shizuku: Hehe. Yes, you are. You're always so kind and incredibly thoughtful.
Shizuku: But... I'm okay, really.
Airi: Really...?
Shizuku: You're right that I'm not completely fine with this...
Shizuku: However...
Shizuku: Nothing will change if I decide not to do this TV appearance with Cheerful * Days.
Shizuku: And if nothing changes... I'll keep having reservations about Cheerful * Days, which will force you all to keep worrying about how I feel...
Shizuku: I really don't want that to happen...
Airi: Shizuku...
Shizuku: So, I see this as a big opportunity.
Shizuku: If we all appear together alongside them and make our segment really fun, that may actually in turn help remedy our worries.
Shizuku: So, please don't worry about me...
Shizuku: More importantly, I want to do everything I can to ensure that our first TV appearance goes well.
Airi: Okay... Sounds like your mind's already made up.
Airi: Then, alright! If you're willing to say that, I'm not pulling any punches!
Shizuku: What?
Airi: MORE MORE JUMP! is making its very first TV appearance... I know our segment's short, but people are gonna remember who we are!
Shizuku: Right!
Minori: I-I-I-I-I'm so nervous... This meeting's really happening...!
Haruka: I understand how you feel, but you should try to relax a little.
Airi: Yeah, the producer won't know what to say if you're that visibly petrified.
Minori: Y-Yeah, I know... I'm trying to settle myself down...
Minori: But...! I forget how you actually do that...!
Airi: This is more serious than I realized...
Shizuku: It's okay, Minori. Whenever you feel this way, just close your eyes and try to focus on yourself.
Minori: On myself...?
Shizuku: Yes. Try to focus on what you want to do for this TV appearance and set everything else aside.
Shizuku: For example, it's good to think of multiple ways to answer each question. Do you know what you're hoping to talk about?
Minori: Oh, um... So... My guess is that they're gonna ask us about how our solo show went...
Minori: Which is when I want to show my appreciation for everyone who came to see us and those who've been supporting us.
Shizuku: And?
Minori: And I have a feeling they're gonna ask us about our outfits. If they do, I really wanna talk about the fans who made them for us.
Shizuku: In summary, Minori, you mainly wish to show our fans just how much we appreciate them...?
Minori: Oh...
Minori: Yeah... Also, if some people decide to become our fans after seeing us on this program...
Minori: I want to tell them that I'm gonna work really hard to inspire hope in them and wish for their support!
Haruka: I take it you feel much better now...?
Minori: Huh...? Whoa, you're right! My heart's still beating pretty hard, but I feel a lot calmer now!
Minori: Your idea worked so well! Thank you, Shizuku!
Airi: Nice one, Shizuku.
Shizuku: Hehe. I'm glad to hear that. I was also really nervous during my first meeting for a TV show, so I know how you feel right now, Minori.
Minori: R-Really?! So, this is normal for everyone?!
Shizuku: Yes. I thought my heart was going to jump out of my chest.
Shizuku: But I gradually got used to it as I started receiving more and more of that sort of work...
Shizuku: So, Minori, I'm sure you'll do just fine.
Minori: I will...?
Minori: Thank goodness! If I can learn to stay cool and calm like you guys...
iHaz Producer: Apologies for the wait! My other meeting went on longer than expected...
Minori: Eep!
Haruka: Oh, you must be the producer for iHaz. It's nice to meet you. My name is Haruka Kiritani of MORE MORE JUMP!
Airi: I'm Airi Momoi, also from MORE MORE JUMP! Thank you for agreeing to meet with us today! We've been looking forward to speaking with you.
Shizuku: And I'm Shizuku Hinomori of MORE MORE JUMP! We really appreciate this opportunity to appear on your program. We promise to do our very best.
Minori: I... U-U-Uhh...!
Minori: I-I'm Minori Hanasato! Thank you very much for contacting us about this offer! And... And, uhh...
Minori: Sh-Shank you for having us today...!!!
Airi: Minori...
iHaz Producer: Hahaha. I can see that you're all full of energy. As I said in my email, I'm very much aware of who you all are.
iHaz Producer: Please, sit. I'll pour us all some tea now. We can talk while munching on some of these snacks.
